v1.1
- Fix: detect hostapd binary explicitly in service run script (/usr/sbin, /usr/bin, PATH)
- Fix: clear error message when hostapd is missing, with install hint
- Fix: cleanup FORWARD iptables rules on ap0 (not wlan0) in finish script
- Fix: stop dnsmasq-ap0 and remove ap0 virtual interface during service stop
- Improvement: setup now attempts to auto-install hostapd via opkg when missing

v1.0
- Initial release
- WiFi AP on ap0 virtual interface (BCM43438 / RPi3)
- Custom SSID + WPA2-PSK via wifi-ap.conf
- dnsmasq DHCP for clients (192.168.0.100-200)
- iptables NAT: ap0 → wwan0 (4G internet sharing)
- Disables connman tethering (conflict with ap0)
- Compatible SetupHelper (install/uninstall/reinstall)
